The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: The rupee will move towards fuller convertibility in a gradual and calibrated manner, finance minister P. Chidamba-ram told the Rajya Sabha today. The movement toward fuller convertibility of rupee will necessarily have to be gradual, sequenced and calibrated to the overall macro-economic situation and emerging needs of the economy, he said in a written reply.

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: The government has collected Rs 66,417 crore through customs and excise duties during the first four months of the current fiscal, an 11.6 per cent rise compared with Rs 59,495 crore in the same period last year. Customs duty receipts rose 19.1 per cent to Rs 31,845 crore and excise duty collections grew 5.5 per cent to Rs 34,571 crore during April to July.

 New Delhi, Aug. 14: The foreign investment promotion board will consider icici Banks proposal to divest 24 per cent stake in icici Financial Services, the banks holding firm for insurance business, at its meeting on Friday.

 Calcutts, Aug. 14: Jay Shree Tea and Industries, a BK Birla group company, has decided to separate its bpo unit in the city Jay Shree Infotech Consultant from itself and divest it to a strategic investor. The company will seek shareholders consent through postal ballot.




